{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"Flexbox","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Glossary/Flexbox","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>Flexbox is the commonly-used name for the <a href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/css-flexbox-1/\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">CSS Flexible Box Layout Module</a>, a layout model for displaying items in a single dimension — as a row or as a column.</p>\n<p>In the specification, Flexbox is described as a layout model for user interface design. The key feature of Flexbox is the fact that items in a flex layout can grow and shrink. Space can be assigned to the items themselves, or distributed between or around the items.</p>\n<p>Flexbox also enables alignment of items on the main or cross axis, thus providing a high level of control over the size and alignment of a group of items.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"See also","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"property_reference","title":"Property reference","isH3":true,"content":"<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/align-content\"><code>align-content</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/align-items\"><code>align-items</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/align-self\"><code>align-self</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/flex\"><code>flex</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/flex-basis\"><code>flex-basis</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/flex-direction\"><code>flex-direction</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/flex-flow\"><code>flex-flow</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/flex-grow\"><code>flex-grow</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/flex-shrink\"><code>flex-shrink</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/flex-wrap\"><code>flex-wrap</code></a></li>\n  <li